<TITLE> DMCH director besieged for hours </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 13 (bdnews24.com)  The fourth-class employees of Dhaka Medical College and Hospital confined its director inside his office for two and a half hours on Wednesday demanding cancellation of the ongoing recruitment of staffs. bdnews24.com's DMCH correspondent reported that at around 1:30pm, 50-60 members of the fourth class employees' association, led by its president Abdul Khalek, besieged Brigadier General Bazle Quader in his room. They demanded termination of the current process of appointing around 200 staffers at the hospital and vowed to continue with their movement until their demand is met. The workers withdrew their siege at around 3pm. An association leader alleged that all the new employees are being recruited according to the lists provided by the pro-Awami League Swadhinata Chikitsak Parisad and Bangladesh Medical Association, doctors' forums. The DMCH employees would not allow their intervention, he said, requesting anonymity . Additional forces of police and Rapid Action Battalion have been deployed at the hospital premises. The protesters also have locked down the gate of the administrative building, but the main entrance and the access to emergency department are open. bdnews24
